 Supabase credentials are already configured in the setup script. Here's what you need to do to enable password reset:

  Quick Setup (3 Steps)

  1. Set the master encryption key

  # Generate a secure key
  export SKUEL_MASTER_KEY=$(openssl rand -base64 32)

  # Add it to your .env file (so it persists)
  echo "SKUEL_MASTER_KEY=$(openssl rand -base64 32)" >> .env

  2. Store Supabase credentials

  poetry run python scripts/setup_supabase_credentials.py

  3. Restart your server

  # Stop current server (Ctrl+C)
  # Restart it
  poetry run python main.py

  Then Test Password Reset

  1. Navigate to: http://localhost:8000/forgot-password
  2. Enter your email: The email you registered with
  3. Check your inbox: Supabase will send a password reset email (may take 1-2 minutes)
  4. Click the link in the email to reset your password

  What Happens Behind the Scenes

  When you submit the forgot password form:
  - Route calls supabase_auth.reset_password_email(email) (line 200 in supabase_auth.py)
  - Supabase sends an email to that address with a secure reset link
  - User clicks link → Supabase shows password reset form
  - User enters new password → Can log in with new password

  Email Provider Notes

  For Development (Right Now):
  - ✅ Supabase's built-in email service works immediately
  - ⚠ Limit: 4 emails/hour per user (plenty for testing)
  - 📧 Emails come from noreply@mail.app.supabase.io

  For Production (Later):
  You can configure custom SMTP in Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Email Settings:
  - SendGrid (free tier: 100 emails/day)
  - Mailgun (free tier: 5,000 emails/month)
  - AWS SES (very cheap)
  - Any SMTP provider

  But for now, no additional setup needed - Supabase handles everything!
